<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36164a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36164a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36164a"> 164(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 6&frac12;<sup>d</sup> per day / per man</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the York Workhouse, where the diet is regulated by the general order of the Local Government Board, the cost of feeding a family consisting of man, wife, and three children works out at almost exactly <mark>6 &frac12;d. per man per day</mark>, <i>calculating the cost of the food at contract prices</i>. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 283</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
